 p_n(t) 
 \frac{d}{dt} p_n(t)  = \lambda \Delta p_n(t) 
 E_m = e^{mk} 
 km - mk = 1 
\Delta = E_1 + E_{-1} - 2 
\large p_{n}\left(t\right) \equiv p_{n}{\rm e}^{-\gamma\mu t\,/a^{2}}
\large a
\large -\left(\mu/a^{2}\right)p_{n} = \Delta p_{n}
\large\tt Assuming
n
 -\,{\mu \over a^{2}}p_{n} = {p_{n + 1} + p_{n -1} - 2p_{n} \over a^{2}}  
 p_{n + 1} + \left(\mu - 2\right)p_{n} + p_{n -1} = 0  
\large \propto \beta^{n}
